"org\">http://bugs.kde.org</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Remote Frame Buffer protocol"
msgstr "Remote Frame Buffer protokol"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter provides a brief description of the Remote Frame Buffer "
"protocol used by &krfb; and by other compatible systems. If you are already "
"familiar with Remote Frame Buffer, you can safely skip this chapter."
msgstr ""
"Ovo poglavlje daje kratak opis Remote Frame Buffer protokola korišten u "
"&krfb; i drugim kompatibilnim sistemima. Ukoliko ste već upoznati sa Remote "
"Frame Buffer protokolom, možete preskočiti ovo poglavlje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The high level implementation of a system using the Remote Frame Buffer "
"protocol is known as Virtual Network Computer, or more often just as "
"<acronym>VNC</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"Visoki nivo implementacije sistema koji korisni Remote Frame Buffer protokol "
"je poznat kao Virtual Network Computer, ili češće samo kao <acronym>VNC</"
"acronym>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remote Frame Buffer (or <acronym>RFB</acronym> for short) is a simple "
"protocol for remote access to graphical user interfaces. It works at the "
"frame-buffer level, which roughly corresponds to the rendered screen image, "
"which means that it can be applied to all windowing systems (including X11, "
"&MacOS; and &Microsoft; &Windows;). Remote Frame Buffer applications exist "
"for many platforms, and can often be freely re-distributed."
msgstr ""
"Remote Frame Buffer (ili kraće <acronym>RFB</acronym>) je jednostavan "
"protokol za daljinski pristup grafičkog korisničkog interfejsa. Ona radi na "
"nivou frame-buffera, što približno odgovara slici na ekranu, što znači da se "
"može primijeniti na sve sisteme (ukuljučujući X11, &MacOS; and &Microsoft; "
"&Windows;). Remote Frame Buffer aplikacije postoje za mnoge platforme, i "
"također mogu se besplatno re-distribuirati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the Remote Frame Buffer protocol, the application that runs on the "
"machine where the user sits (containing the display, keyboard and pointer) "
"is called the client. The application that runs on the machine where the "
"framebuffer is located (which is running the windowing system and "
"applications that the user is remotely controlling) is called the server. "
"&krfb; is the &kde; server for the Remote Frame Buffer protocol. &krdc; is "
"the &kde; client for the Remote Frame Buffer protocol."
msgstr ""
"U Remote Frame Buffer protokolu, aplikacija koja radi na uređaju gdje je "
"korisnik (sadrži monitor, tastaturu i miš) se naziva klijent. Aplikacija "
"koja radi na uređajuu na kojem se nalazi Framebuffer (na kojoj je pokrenut "
"sistem i aplikacije kojima korisnik vrši daljinsku kontrolu) naziva se "
"server. &krfb; je &kde; server za Remote Frame Buffer protokool. &krdc; je "
"&kde; klijent za Remote Frame Buffer protokol."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It takes a reasonable amount of network traffic to send an image of the "
"framebuffer, so Remote Frame Buffer works best over high bandwidth links, "
"such as a local area network. It is still possible to use &krfb; over other "
"links, but performance is unlikely to be as good."
msgstr ""
"Potrebno je imati razumnu količinu mrežnog prometa da biste poslali sliku o "
"Framebufferu, Remote Frame Buffer najbolje radi preko visoko propusnih veza, "
"kao što su lokalne mreže. Ipak je moguće koristiti &krfb; u odnosu na druge "
"veze, ali učinak je malo vjerovatno dobar."

